{"id":913,"date":"2020-12-22T12:24:58","date_gmt":"2020-12-22T12:24:58","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/?p=913"},"modified":"2020-12-22T12:24:58","modified_gmt":"2020-12-22T12:24:58","slug":"livestream-update-22-12-20","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/2020\/12\/22\/livestream-update-22-12-20\/","title":{"rendered":"Livestream Update (22\/12\/20)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Please note that the <strong>information below is not final<\/strong>, and certain aspects may be <strong>subject to change<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>CONTENTS<\/strong>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Schedule<\/li><li>Balance Update &#8211; Imperials<\/li><li>Alliance War &#8211; Mahaha, The Maniacal Spectre<ol><li>Titan Overview<\/li><li>Relic Overview<\/li><li>Milestone Rewards<\/li><li>Alliance Rewards<\/li><li>Chosen Titans and Boost Relic<\/li><\/ol><\/li><li>Altar of Everything<\/li><li>DoT Content Creators<\/li><li>Unofficial Social Channels<\/li><li>Official Social Channels<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>SCHEDULE<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We\u2019ve added a new section to the website &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/events\/\">CALENDAR<\/a><em>. <\/em>This can be accessed via the top tab menu, and will be kept up to date with all upcoming events in Dawn of Titans.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <strong>List <\/strong>view to see all future events and their start and end times, and use <strong>Month<\/strong> view to get a calendar overview of each month.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, use the <strong>+Export Events <\/strong>button to download the calendar as a .ics file that can be imported into your own calendar applications (e.g. Outlook).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>BALANCE UPDATE &#8211; Imperials<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-rounded\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh4.googleusercontent.com\/FAy-ihtwAFOh4orOKWAd635xxHlLf5O0Tq9vN0FvQaBjC5AIEJs8Gr4W7GCura92fl1wP-2v0IrRxytnToHsN8Om03cick-3hQCYoqZGuEtFTOJ-U1efLD8AO5quoGBAE6gDygEJ\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>After reading player feedback and analysing troop usage across all levels, we\u2019ve made some changes to Imperial troops that are live in-game now.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These changes are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>+5%<\/strong> Health<\/li><li><strong>+5%<\/strong> Base Damage<\/li><li><strong>+10%<\/strong> Armor Piercing<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>ALLIANCE WAR &#8211; <\/strong><strong><em>Mahaha, The Maniacal Spectre<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh3.googleusercontent.com\/OwBfb35AL8YdtjTPiNaGNQIWHw9cD0ym1TQj08KUR0tuU-uzYwZYg2IPciob3WQ9nFDBrYhT2ncy1Z_nDj-uLIPpqAD_lRMtVx5U1ZVrxJXDVL9tdUzNP5JpK1MXt6R36mN85gb0\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>STARTS:<\/strong> 24th December, 15:00 UTC<br><strong>ENDS:<\/strong> 28th December, 09:00 UTC<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Whilst the Elithen townsfolk solemnly prepared for the coming winter, their armies gathered at the palace, desperate for an audience with their Queen before the frost took a hold over their land. Progenitor sat at her throne, silent. An air of unease filled the hall, and Matarus, bravest of the commanders and former leader of the southern tribe, stepped forward and gracefully lowered his head&#8230;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cYour majesty, we request your aid. The winter winds are here, and our people are vanishing by the day. An unseen threat travels within the frost, and we must eradicate it before it\u2019s too late\u201d.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Progenitor stood, and without a word spoken, she descended the throne and took up her sword and shield. Before making her way out of the palace, she turned to Matarus and presented him her crown &#8211; Matarus bowed and accepted his Queen\u2019s silent request, he would take up the throne until her return. The fearless monarch departed, and soon reached the edge of the city, where she paused high up the towering walls of ice that protected it. She closed her eyes and listened &#8211; through the piercing gales she heard a faint, unnatural noise, an almost demonic laughter. Masking her fear, she descended the wall, and headed straight into the uncharted tundra beyond the city gates&#8230;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>On the third day, Progenitor reached the foothills of an ancient mountain outpost lost to the harsh winters of decades past, and began her ascent. At the summit, she scanned the frozen wastes, and to her horror, she made out what appeared to be the remains of countless Elithen Imperial troops. On each of their lifeless faces sat a twisted, frozen grin.. The Ice Queen dropped her weapon, numbed by the unsettling sight of so many of her people\u2019s demise. Suddenly, an aura of immense power enveloped the outpost and complete silence befell the land. A piercing cackle echoed through the icy peaks and reverberated the stone-cold earth. Progenitor froze where she stood &#8211; in all the millenia she had lived, she had never felt so terrified.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>As the screeching laughter drew closer, the hunched figure of a deformed Titan slowly emerged from the blizzard. His frost-ridden body thawed and crackled with Nexus energy. Progenitor looked on as a corrupted mist surrounded and then engorged the remains of her brethren. Mahaha let out a deafening shriek, reanimating the dead before her very eyes, and commanding them back to life. They rose, emanating with the corruption, and assembled in formation with their spears aimed aggressively at their former Queen. As the wights began to march threateningly towards her, she closed her eyes. With the knowledge only an ancient being such as herself could possess, she accepted defeat, and with it, the inevitable demise of her kingdom.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The maniacal Dragonslayer of the frozen tundra is finally here! <strong>MAHAHA<\/strong> arrives in the Shattered Kingdoms, bringing with him the power of Freeze and Corrupted Imperial forces.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"916\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaSkills-1024x916.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-914\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaSkills-1024x916.png 1024w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaSkills-300x268.png 300w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaSkills-768x687.png 768w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaSkills.png 1342w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Corrupted Imperials <\/strong>have the following stat changes when compared with standard Imperial troops:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>+50%<\/strong> Health<\/li><li><strong>+50%<\/strong> Base Damage<\/li><li><strong>+30%<\/strong> Movement Speed<\/li><li>Decreased Armor Piercing<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Get these signature <strong>Relics<\/strong> and many more from the Milestone rewards:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"665\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaRelics-1024x665.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-915\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/MahahaRelics-1024x665.png 1024w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-cont